<P><center>
<H2>And My Daughter Won't Be a Hypocrite Either . . .</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>






"There'll be some changes made now that Madonna is a mommy. Besides deciding to leave New York (as we reported first), the <I>Evita</I> star says she's cut loose her 'frivolous' friends. Gone from her life are 'certain people that I [no longer] found amusing and interesting.'
<P>
"She also tells <I>Redbook</I> that: She won't let her daughter, Lourdes, watch TV ('TV's poison,' says the MTV staple) . . . that she doesn't want Lourdes surfing the Internet ('The people who like going on-line the best are people who can't sustain a relationship for more than five minutes.') . . . and that she will raise Lourdes a Catholic (though she'll tell her the stories in the Bible are not, 'like, the rule')."
<P>
<I>New York Daily News</I>, December 9, 1996




</blockquote>
