<!-----------------Townhall------------------------------>
<I>December 3, 1996</I></center>
<BR>
<BR>

<P><center>
<H2>Bad Behavior on the Florida Supreme Court</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>







	



	"Florida prison doors will swing wide open for 445 murderers, sex offenders, kidnappers, and child abusers beginning today after a state Supreme Court restored time off for good behavior for the state's most violent offenders, prison officials said. Attorney General Bob Butterworth said he'll appeal to the U.S. Supreme Court, but by then hundreds of inmates will have been released. Officials are trying to determine who will be freed immediately. The pending releases have generated protests from the public. 'We've done everything we can to keep them locked up,' Corrections Department spokeswoman Debbie Buchanan said. 'We don't have any choice. Our hands are tied.' "
<P>
John bacon, <I>USA Today</I>, November 6, 1996
</blockquote>
<!------------------------------------------------------------>
<P>
