<P><center>
<H2>Call Her Ms. Fix-It</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>




	"Just two months after the White House downplayed Hillary Rodham Clinton's second-term role, the controversial First Lady is now saying she'll have a 'formal' presence in crafting welfare policy. . . .
<P>
	"Mrs. Clinton has kept a low profile since the health-plan fiasco and denied during the 1996 campaign that she'd have a new policy role."
<P>
Thomas Galvin, <I>New York Post</I>, November 25, 1996
</blockquote>
<!------------------------------------------------------------>
