<P><center>
<H2>Too Good for Government Work</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>




	"Seattle  Helen Sanwell, a King County parks manager who worked overtime without pay, has been suspended for six days for insubordination, beginning Wednesday. Officials said she'd been warned about overtime work, which they say violates federal law."
<P>

<I>USA Today</I>, November 4, 1996

</blockquote>
