<H2>Owtrayj do joor</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>



	"Leesburg, Va.  the predominantly Democratic school board here defends a widley used teaching technique called 'whole language.' The philoosphy seems reaosnable enough: Throw out thse boringphoniucs drills and put literature in the hands of kids. Let them figure out words in context. Let them write unbound, initialy at least, by the tedious rules of splling and grammar. So what if elephant is spelled 'elifant'? "






<P>


Christina Duff, <I>Wall Street Journal</I>, October 30, 1996

</blockquote>
